OL,3,GStrathclyde
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FMainly dry with some bright or
OL,6,Fsunny intervals although cloudy across
OL,7,Fthe Central Belt and south at times. A
OL,8,Ffew showers breaking out by afternoon.
OL,9,
OL,10,CTonight:FAny showers slowly dying out
OL,11,Fthis evening. Then the rest of the
OL,12,Fnight will be dry with variable
OL,13,Famounts of cloud. A cold night with
OL,14,Fpatchy frost.
OL,15,
OL,16,CSunday:FMost of the day will be dry
OL,17,Fand bright. Outbreaks of rain will
OL,18,Fspread into Argyll by late afternoon
OL,19,Fand elsewhere in the evening.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
